# Local Dev Environment Gotchas

Learned the hard way debugging local setup — check these before assuming code is broken.

## Two separate virtualenvs

- Root `.venv` — for `bin/insummery`, `app/mcp_server.py`, pytest, evals.
- `functions/venv` — a **separate** venv Firebase's emulator creates from
  `functions/requirements.txt`. Going stale here causes emulator function-load
  failures like `ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'opentelemetry.instrumentation'`.
  Fix: `.\functions\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pip install -r functions\requirements.txt`.
- On Windows, a bare `python` on `PATH` may resolve to a global install, not
  `.venv`. Always activate `.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1` first, or invoke
  `.venv\Scripts\python.exe` explicitly. Symptom of forgetting: missing-module
  errors for packages that ARE installed in `.venv`.
- After adding a dependency to `pyproject.toml`, rerun
  `.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pip install -e .` — it doesn't happen automatically.

## `.env` files (all gitignored, none committed)

- Root `.env` — loaded automatically by `app/cli.py` and `app/mcp_server.py`
  via `python-dotenv` (added explicitly; not automatic in a fresh repo).
- `functions/.env.local` — loaded automatically by `firebase emulators:start`
  for the Functions emulator only.
- Templates live in `.env.example` at the repo root.

## GCP project ID: `in-summery`, not `insummery-ai`

- The real GCP project (Vertex AI, OAuth clients, Secret Manager) is
  **`in-summery`**.
- `insummery-ai` is only a Firebase emulator placeholder from `.firebaserc` —
  it doesn't necessarily exist as a real GCP project. Don't `gcloud config set
  project insummery-ai` or set `GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT=insummery-ai`; use
  `in-summery`.
- Vertex AI needs ADC, not an API key: `gcloud auth application-default login`
  then `gcloud auth application-default set-quota-project in-summery`.

## Google Calendar OAuth: two flows need two client types

- CLI/MCP (`app/mcp_server.py`, `InstalledAppFlow.run_local_server`) needs a
  **Desktop app** OAuth client (loopback redirect is implicit, nothing to
  register). Credentials go in root `.env`.
- Web app via Firebase emulator (`functions/main.py`) needs a **Web
  application** OAuth client with
  `http://localhost:5000/api/oauth/google-calendar/callback` registered under
  Authorized redirect URIs, or you'll hit `Error 400: redirect_uri_mismatch`.
  Credentials go in `functions/.env.local`.

## Weave/W&B

- `WEAVE_PROJECT` must be `entity/project` (e.g. `your-wandb-entity/insummery-ai`),
  not just the project name — find your entity at wandb.ai.
- The project doesn't need to be pre-created in the W&B UI; `weave.init()`
  creates it automatically under that entity on first successful run.

See `README.md` for the full setup walkthroughs these notes summarize.
